<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <nav class="mb-6">
    <%= link_to "â† Back to Help", help_path, class: "text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" %>
  </nav>

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Data Model</h1>

  <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
    Understanding how political data is organized in Candidata helps you navigate and 
    interpret the information effectively.
  </p>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Core Entities</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-2">People</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
          Individual politicians, whether they are current officeholders, former officials, 
          or candidates who have run for office.
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          <strong>Key fields:</strong> Name, party affiliation, state, photo, websites, biographical data
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Offices</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
          Political positions that can be held, such as "U.S. Senator from Texas" or 
          "Mayor of Chicago". Offices exist independently of who holds them.
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          <strong>Key fields:</strong> Title, level (federal/state/local), branch (executive/legislative/judicial), jurisdiction
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-700 mb-2">Officeholders</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
          The connection between a person and an office they hold (or held). Includes 
          term dates, allowing us to track who held which office and when.
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          <strong>Key fields:</strong> Start date, end date, term end date, next election date, contact info
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-orange-700 mb-2">Candidates</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
          When a person runs for an office in a specific election. Tracks campaign 
          information and election outcomes (won, lost, pending).
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          <strong>Key fields:</strong> Contest, party at time, incumbent status, outcome, vote tally
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2">Parties</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
          Political parties that officials and candidates are affiliated with. A person 
          can be associated with multiple parties (e.g., fusion tickets) with one marked as primary.
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          <strong>Includes:</strong> Democratic Party, Republican Party, plus 20+ minor and territory-specific parties
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-700 mb-2">Bodies</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
          Legislative bodies, councils, boards, and courts that group related offices together.
          Examples include "U.S. Senate", "California State Assembly", or "Cook County Board of Commissioners".
        </p>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          <strong>Key fields:</strong> Name, level, branch, state, chamber type (upper/lower), seats count
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Government Levels</h2>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700">Federal</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-blue-600 mt-1">President, Congress, Federal Courts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700">State</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-green-600 mt-1">Governors, State Legislators, State Courts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-700">Local</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-purple-600 mt-1">County, City, School Districts</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Government Branches</h2>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">Executive</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">
          Presidents, Governors, Mayors, County Executives, Sheriffs, Attorneys General
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">Legislative</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">
          Senators, Representatives, State Legislators, City Council Members
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
        <div class="font-bold text-gray-900">Judicial</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">
          Supreme Court Justices, Appeals Court Judges, District Judges
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Districts & Jurisdictions</h2>
    
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
      Political boundaries that define where officials serve and who can vote for them.
    </p>

    <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200">
      <thead class="bg-gray-50">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase">District Type</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase">Count</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase">Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="bg-white divide-y divide-gray-200">
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">Congressional Districts</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">435</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">U.S. House seats, plus 6 at-large states</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">State Senate Districts</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">~1,970</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">Upper chambers of state legislatures</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">State House Districts</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">~4,700</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">Lower chambers of state legislatures</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">Counties</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">~3,100</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-gray-600">County-level jurisdictions</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Open Civic Data IDs (OCDIDs)</h2>
    
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
      We use standardized Open Civic Data IDs to uniquely identify jurisdictions and districts. 
      These IDs follow a hierarchical pattern:
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-900 text-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <div class="mb-2"><span class="text-green-400">// Congressional District</span></div>
      <div class="mb-4">ocd-division/country:us/state:tx/cd:1</div>
      
      <div class="mb-2"><span class="text-green-400">// State Senate District</span></div>
      <div class="mb-4">ocd-division/country:us/state:ca/sldu:15</div>
      
      <div class="mb-2"><span class="text-green-400">// State House District</span></div>
      <div class="mb-4">ocd-division/country:us/state:ny/sldl:42</div>
      
      <div class="mb-2"><span class="text-green-400">// County</span></div>
      <div>ocd-division/country:us/state:fl/county:miami-dade</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
